HSBC Holdings to Pull Out of Chile, Peru, Poland, Sky News Says

-- B y   J a s o n   W e b b   a n d   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-05-07T13:37:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-07/hsbc-holdings-to-pull-out-of-chile-peru-poland-sky-news-says.html
HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  will announce plans
to withdraw from Chile, Peru and Poland as it focuses on bigger,
more profitable markets, Sky News reported on a blog.  HSBC Chief Executive Officer Stuart Gulliver will also
unveil next week “huge” cost-cutting measures to reduce middle
management, the blog said. HSBC press officials in London
couldn’t be reached today by telephone.  Editor:  Mike Anderson .  To contact the reporter on this story:
